  "texts": [
    "Due to O(N 2) number of comparisons required for the full comparison matrix, it might be practical to only consider a subset of comparisons.",
    "Figure 4 shows the downstream Spearman correlation for SummEval coherency, when averaged over 50 runs, for different comparison selection strategies.",
    "Of the three schemes, we observe that for small R (i.e.",
    "less than half the total number of comparisons) selecting comparisons with no repeats leads to a marginal improvement over random selection.",
    "Further, by using the symmetric selection scheme, despite the number of comparisons being half that of no-repeat (although each comparison is done twice, once in each permutation), interestingly there is only a performance difference of 1 in terms of Spearman."
  ],
